PrometheusPraxisCodingTask2026v1
  taskid   PPX-TASK-0001
  title    Wire eco_restoration_shard spine into Prometheus-Praxis
  priority P0
  status   PLANNED
  ownerteam Prometheus-Core
  dependson []
  summary  "Create explicit spine modules and docs that bind Prometheus-Praxis to eco_restoration_shard and sibling repos as the README promises."[file:2]
  codetargets
    Prometheus-Praxis/ARCHITECTURE.md
    Prometheus-Praxis/src/spine/mod.rs
    Prometheus-Praxis/src/spine/e_restoration_spine.rs
  dbtargets
    Eco-Fort/db/ecoconstellationindex.sql
    Eco-Fort/db/repoindexrestoration.sql
  alntargets
    workspacealn/alnPrometheusPraxisCore.v1.aln
    workspacealn-specs/alnEcoRepoIndex2026v1.aln
  kerimpact "K E R"
  acceptancecriteria "ARCHITECTURE.md lists concrete crates, ALN shards, and SQL files that implement the execution-layer role; spine modules expose non-actuating functions that map eco_restoration_shard KER/Lyapunov math into Prometheus-Praxis without duplicating residual logic."[file:2]
  notes "Keep spine modules thin, declarative, and governance-first; avoid adding new Rust crates for this task and rely on existing eco_restoration_shard crates and ALN specs."[file:2]

PrometheusPraxisCodingTask2026v1
  taskid   PPX-TASK-0002
  title    Implement governance_flag B_f, H_f, G_f kernel
  priority P0
  status   PLANNED
  ownerteam Prometheus-Governance
  dependson [PPX-TASK-0001]
  summary  "Create non-actuating Rust and ALN modules for blast-radius B_f, health/reward H_f, and governance flag G_f = max(B_f,H_f), aligned with README semantics."[file:2][file:1]
  codetargets
    Prometheus-Praxis/src/governance_flag.rs
    Prometheus-Praxis/src/ker/ker_superloop.rs
    Prometheus-Praxis/tests/governance_flag_tests.rs
  dbtargets
    Eco-Fort/db/planeweightsschema.sql
    Eco-Fort/db/blastradiusspine.sql
  alntargets
    workspacealn-specs/alnPrometheusGovernanceFlags2026v1.aln
    workspacealn-specs/aln-specsPlaneWeightsShard2026v1.aln
  kerimpact "K E R"
  acceptancecriteria "governance_flag.rs exposes pure functions that, given KER triads, residual V_t, and topology risk, compute B_f, H_f, G_f with documented thresholds; tests and Kani harnesses prove that non-offsettable planes and blast-radius limits obey monotone safety evolution and match Eco-Fort planeweights and blast-radius specs."[file:1][file:22]
  notes "No IO or actuator calls; map results into small structs and ALN particles; use rust-version 1.85, edition 2024, and !forbid(unsafe_code)."

